name: Pain Immunity: Worried the Villains Aren’t Twisted Enough
summary: 【Dark Humor + Comedy + Ruthless + Global Survival + Unconventional Thinking + Single Love Interest + Semi-Invincible + Smart Power Fantasy (or Dumb Fun)】A global horror game descends upon the world. The chosen ones must participate in challenges of inhuman difficulty. In these torment-filled games, there is also a chance to gain extraordinary power.Life or death. A single step to the top—or losing everything.However, Lu Ce, who has never felt pain since childhood, is completely unfazed by this hellish game. In fact, he even finds it amusing. Right from the start, he awakens the “Chosen of Agony” system.Chosen of Agony—Endure theoretical torment and suffering to gain attribute points!Pain = Attribute Points + I Have No Pain = Unlimited Points!When tasked with retrieving a key from a boiling oil vat, Lu Ce doesn’t hesitate to reach in—and even suggests switching the oil to 98% concentrated sulfuric acid.Faced with the choice of drowning or cutting off his shackled leg to escape, Lu Ce pauses for a moment… then decides to leave the locked left leg alone for now and saw off his right leg first!【Bro, who is this guy? Just watching him makes me feel pain, and he’s over there laughing?!】【The best way to conquer fear is to become fear itself. Clearly, he’s mastered that.】【Everyone else gets tortured by the game. Lu God tortures the game itself!】【I watched one of his gameplay videos and had nightmares for a month…】Lu Ce: “A test of human nature? For me, it’s just an experience! Got anything else?”“I only have one concern coming here: your imagination for torture methods isn’t wild enough.”“As villains, I really think you guys should be more twisted. Otherwise… it’ll be my turn, hehehe~~”
author: 陷阵营营长
